<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
<br>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p lang="is" dir="ltr"><a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Sicario?src=hash">#Sicario</a> composer jóhann jóhannsson is the next big thing in film music.<a href="https://t.co/Fl7T4ounKR">https://t.co/Fl7T4ounKR</a><a href="https://twitter.com/JohannJohannss">@JohannJohannss</a> <a href="https://t.co/COXQgb8hHY">pic.twitter.com/COXQgb8hHY</a></p>&mdash; Soundtracks.io (@soundtracks_io) <a href="https://twitter.com/soundtracks_io/status/705135996447399936">March 2, 2016</a></blockquote>
<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>

      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-4 jobs">
         
        
        
        <% @jobs.each do |job| %>
            <div class="job">
            
            <h2><%= image_tag "movies.png", :class => "movie-icon" %><%= link_to job.title %></h2>
            <p><%= job.url %></p>
            <p><%= job.details %></p>

            <p><%= job.company %>

            </div>
            <hr class="black">
          <% end %>


        <div class="add-a-job btn-group">  
        <p><%= link_to "ADD A JOB", new_job_path, :class => "btn btn-success align-center" %></p>
      </div>


        <p><%= paginate @jobs %></p>
      </div>

    <div class="col-md-3 box">
      <h2>ABOUT</h2>
      Soundtracks.io is a free jobs board for Film, TV, and Game composers.

      <h2>ADD A JOB</h2>
      Send an email to info@soundtrack.io or a tweet to <a class="a-normal" href="https://twitter.com/soundtracks_io">@soundtracks_io</a> with some of the following details: <br>
      <ol>
        <li>Title of Job </li>
        <li>Company/Project/Client</li>
        <li>Brief details </li>
        <li>URL (if exists)</li>
        <li>Contact details
      </ol>
    
      If you would like to use a tweet as a job posting simply mention in your tweet to @soundtracks_io that you'd like a retweet!
      
      <div>

      <div class="col-md-1"></div>
    </div>
</div>
